SIMPLE: air_cooling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Air cooling
<hw>Air cooling</hw>. <def>In devices generating heat, such as
gasoline-engine motor vehicles, the cooling of the device by increasing
its radiating surface by means of ribs or radiators, and placing it so
that it is exposed to a current of air. Cf. <er>Water
cooling</er>.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Air"-cooled`</wf>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Aircraft</ent>⟦br⟧
